==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rambutan
<hw>Ram*bu"tan</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧m*b⟦oomac⟧"t⟦acr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Malay <ets>ramb⟦umac⟧tan</ets>, fr. <ets>rambut</ets> hair of the
head.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A Malayan fruit produced by the tree
<spn>Nephelium lappaceum</spn>, and closely related to the litchi nut.
It is bright red, oval in shape, covered with coarse hairs (whence the
name), and contains a pleasant acid pulp. Called also
<altname>ramboostan</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rameal</ent>⟦br⟧
